---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BasicBitch.astro';
const pageTitle = "Senior Product Designer";

import Thumb from '../../components/Thumb.astro';
const allPosts = Object.values(import.meta.glob('../work/**/*.md', { eager: true }));

const featuredCompanies = [
  'mmf',
  'research',
  'pacific-grove-exhibition-design',
  'mantasponsorship',
  'piper'
];

const featuredPosts = allPosts
  .filter(post =>
    featuredCompanies.includes(post.frontmatter.slug)
  )
  .sort((a, b) =>
    featuredCompanies.indexOf(a.frontmatter.slug) -
    featuredCompanies.indexOf(b.frontmatter.slug)
  );


---
<BaseLayout pageTitle={pageTitle}>
	<div class="grid">
		<div class="hello">
			<p>Hello iNaturalist.</p> 
			<p>I am a product designer with deep roots in citizen science and science communication — and iNaturalist is a platform I have long admired and used. I have designed data visualizations for marine megafauna citizen science projects, authored peer-reviewed research, led underwater biodiversity surveys, and built a museum exhibition around species population loss. My work sits at the intersection of rigorous science and design that brings a wider audience into that science.
			</p>
		</div>
	</div>

	<hr>

	<h3>My scientific and educational work</h3>

	<div class="grid works">
	  	{featuredPosts.map((post: any) => 
	  		<Thumb 
	  			url={post.url} 
	  			title={post.frontmatter.title} 
	  			src={post.frontmatter.src} 
	  			alt={post.frontmatter.alt} 
	  			category={post.frontmatter.category} 
	  			company={post.frontmatter.company}
	  			summary={post.frontmatter.summary}
	  		/>
	  	)}
	</div>

	<div class="grid quotes">
		<h3>What my coworkers are saying</h3>
		<div class="card">
			<div class="pic">
				<img src="/media/demane.jpg">
			</div>
			<div class="text">
				<p class="quote">"Dan is a brilliant UX developer, and a great person. I have had the opportunity to work with Dan over a few years on a number of projects and he is often the most valuable member of the project team."</p>
				<p class="name">Demane Rodney</p>
				<p class="role">Executive Director at Morgan Stanley</p>
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class="card">
			<div class="pic">
				<img src="/media/ben.jpg">
			</div>
			<div class="text">
				<p class="quote">"I know him as someone who I can count on to deliver not only excellent design solutions, but powerful digital strategies to back them up. He's a pleasure to work with, and will deliver the goods every time."</p>
				<p class="name">Ben Thompson</p>
				<p class="role">UX Director at Kaiser Permanente</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>

	<div class="grid skills">
		<div class="card">
			<img src="/media/realresearch.jpg">
			<h2>Grounded in science</h2>
			<p>My background spans data collection, statistical analysis, and formal publication across the ocean sciences and human health. I have led underwater biodiversity surveys, co-authored peer-reviewed papers, and visualized complex ecological datasets for academic and public audiences. This rigor carries directly into my product work — where I insist on evidence before conclusions and precision in what we measure and communicate.</p>
		</div>
		<div class="card">
			<img src="/media/goodwithpeople.jpg">
			<h2>Science communicator</h2>
			<p>Getting people excited about nature is a design challenge. I have created museum exhibitions, interactive citizen science dashboards, and conservation campaigns that connect diverse audiences — from local dive communities to global donors — to the species and systems that need their attention. Clear, honest storytelling is at the heart of everything I build.</p>
		</div>
		<div class="card">
			<img src="/media/AIDriven.jpg">
			<h2>AI driven</h2>
			<p>In 2022 I began using AI to accelerate the analysis of large environmental datasets. Today, the diversity of AI tools has exploded and I use them in every step of software development. From engineering and design to marketing and operations, I'm now getting more done than ever.</p>
		</div>
		<div class="card">
			<img src="/media/multisector.jpg">
			<h2>Citizen science by design</h2>
			<p>I understand citizen science from the inside — as a collector, an analyst, and a designer of tools that make data collection easier and more enjoyable for volunteers. I have improved collection workflows in the field by talking directly to the people doing the work, and I design interfaces that fit naturally into the rhythms of curious, passionate communities.</p>
		</div>
	</div>

	<div class="letstalk" id="contact">
		<h1>I would love to talk about iNaturalist and how my background in science, design, and citizen science could contribute to your mission.</h1>
		<p>I'm available via <a href="mailto:hello@danvallentyne.com">email</a>.</p>
	</div>



</BaseLayout>
